{"cursor":"11515","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Weapon |name=Beretta Model 12 |image= |caption=Beretta M12 without\nmagazine. |origin= |type=Submachine gun  |is_ranged=yes\n|is_UK=  |service=1959âpresent\n|used_by=See [[Beretta M12#Users|Users]] |wars=Vietnam War, The Troubles,\nAfghanistan War, Libyan civil war  |designer=Beretta\n|design_date=1950â1959 |manufacturer=Beretta, Taurus,\nDefence Industries Corporation, MAS, PT Pindad |production_date=1959âpresent |number= |variants=See [[Beretta M12#Variants|Variants]]  |weight=Metal stock:\n*  (M12)\n*  (M12S)\n*  (M12S2) Wood stock:\n*  (M12)\n*  (M12S) |length=Fixed stock:  Folding stock:\n*  stock extended\n*  stock folded |part_length= |width= |height= |crew=\n    |cartridge=9Ã19mm Parabellum |action=Blowback |rate=550\n   rounds/min |velocity=\n   |range=100 to 200 m sight adjustments |max_range= |feed=20, 32, 40-round\n   detachable box magazine |sights=Two-position flip\n   rear aperture, shrouded front post sight radius }}\n\nThe 'Beretta Model 12' is a 9Ã19mm Parabellum caliber submachine gun designed by\nBeretta. The production started in 1962, the first users were the Italian\nCarabinieri and the Italian State Police even though in limited number, only in\n1978 it was widely issued replacing the old Beretta MAB. Oddly enough in 1962\nthe Italian Army bought a limited number of Franchi LF57 submachine gun, judged\nbetter than the M12 but never issued to the troops, and only in 1992 the M12S2\nvariant was introduced also if in very limited number. The Italian Air Force,\ninstead, bought a large number of M12S and M12S2 for the airport security units.\nHowever the weapon had a higher initial success in the Arab countries and South\nAmerica. Its debut in combat came during the Tet Offensive in 1968 when the\nMarines guarding the U.S. embassy in Saigon repelled the assault by the Viet\nCong using the Beretta M12. It is also used by various South American and\nAfrican countries, and made under license in Brazil\nby Taurus and in Indonesia by PT Pindad.\n","linknr":341,"url":"Beretta_M12","recorded":1375074087,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Beretta_M12&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Beretta_M12&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Beretta_M12.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Beretta_M12.jpg/300px-Beretta_M12.jpg","/wiki/Magazine_(firearms)","/wiki/Submachine_gun","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/03/Flag_of_Italy.svg/23px-Flag_of_Italy.svg.png","/wiki/Italy","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Beretta_M12#Users","/wiki/Vietnam_War","/wiki/The_Troubles","/wiki/Afghan_civil_war","/wiki/Libyan_civil_war","/wiki/Beretta","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Beretta","/wiki/Taurus_(manufacturer)","/wiki/Manufacture_d%27armes_de_Saint-%C3%89tienne","/wiki/Pindad","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Beretta_M12#Variants","#cite_note-miller2001-1","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Gun_barrel","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Cartridge_(firearms)","/wiki/9x19mm_Parabellum","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Firearm_action","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Rate_of_fire","#cite_note-miller2001-1","/wiki/Muzzle_velocity","#cite_note-miller2001-1"